{"title":"Automatically commit code by Jenkins","slug":"2019/05/auto-bump-build-version","date":"2019-05-12T13:21:55.000Z","updated":"2020-05-23T16:08:05.056Z","comments":true,"path":"api/articles/2019/05/auto-bump-build-version.json","excerpt":null,"covers":null,"content":"<p>When we need to release a product, we should change copyright, build version, release month, release note…<br>How to modify multiple files automatically?<br>I used a Jenkins pipeline project, the project is parameterized(string parameter) and regular expressions to implement. </p>\n<ol>\n<li><p>Here is the string parameter for copyright:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Name: copyright</li>\n<li>Default Value: 1995—2019</li>\n<li>Description: Copyright format:1995—2019  <figure class=\"highlight plain\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">stage(&#39;change copyrigh&#39;) &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    steps &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">        sh label: &#39;&#39;, script: &#39;sed -i -E &quot;s&#x2F;(1995—[0-9]&#123;4&#125;)&#x2F;$&#123;copyright&#125;&#x2F;&quot; 1033&#x2F;AutoRun.ini&#39;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    &#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p>Here is the string parameter for build version:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Name: build_version</li>\n<li>Default Value: 1.2.2.1002</li>\n<li>Description: build version format: 1.2.2.1002  <figure class=\"highlight plain\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">stage(&#39;change build version&#39;) &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    steps &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">        sh label: &#39;&#39;, script: &#39;sed -i -E &quot;s&#x2F;([0-9].[0-9].[0-9].[0-9]&#123;4&#125;)&#x2F;$&#123;build_version&#125;&#x2F;&quot; 1033&#x2F;AutoRun.ini&#39;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    &#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p>Here is the string parameter for build version:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Name: release_month</li>\n<li>Default Value: May 2019</li>\n<li>Description: release month format: May 2019  <figure class=\"highlight plain\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">stage(&#39;change release month&#39;) &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    steps &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">        sh label: &#39;&#39;, script: &#39;&#39;&#39;</span><br><span class=\"line\">        sed -i -E &quot;s&#x2F;([a-z]* 20[0-9]&#123;2&#125;)&#x2F;$&#123;release_month&#125;&#x2F;&quot; 1033&#x2F;AutoRun.ini</span><br><span class=\"line\">        sed -i -E &quot;s&#x2F;([a-z]* 20[0-9]&#123;2&#125;)&#x2F;$&#123;release_month&#125;&#x2F;&quot; 1033&#x2F;MainMenu.ini</span><br><span class=\"line\">        &#39;&#39;&#39;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    &#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><p>push change to Git</p>\n <figure class=\"highlight plain\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br><span class=\"line\">9</span><br><span class=\"line\">10</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">stage(&#39;git push to Git&#39;) &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    steps &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">        sshagent([&#39;8dd766ba-ac0f-4302-afa8-bee59c726dee&#39;]) &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">            sh(&quot;git add 1033&#x2F;AutoRun.ini&quot;)</span><br><span class=\"line\">            sh(&quot;git add 1033&#x2F;MainMenu.ini&quot;)</span><br><span class=\"line\">            sh(&quot;git commit -m &#39;Bld # $&#123;build_version&#125;&#39;&quot;)</span><br><span class=\"line\">            sh(&quot;git push -u origin master&quot;)</span><br><span class=\"line\">        &#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\">    &#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n</li>\n<li><p>Whole Jenkins Pipeline looks like:</p>\n <figure class=\"highlight plain\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br><span class=\"line\">9</span><br><span class=\"line\">10</span><br><span class=\"line\">11</span><br><span class=\"line\">12</span><br><span class=\"line\">13</span><br><span class=\"line\">14</span><br><span class=\"line\">15</span><br><span class=\"line\">16</span><br><span class=\"line\">17</span><br><span class=\"line\">18</span><br><span class=\"line\">19</span><br><span class=\"line\">20</span><br><span class=\"line\">21</span><br><span class=\"line\">22</span><br><span class=\"line\">23</span><br><span class=\"line\">24</span><br><span class=\"line\">25</span><br><span class=\"line\">26</span><br><span class=\"line\">27</span><br><span class=\"line\">28</span><br><span class=\"line\">29</span><br><span class=\"line\">30</span><